resources.description: A MATLAB mat file containing one million RNA sequences and their structures.
resources.name: 10^6 RNA sequences and structures

resources.description: This file contains tab separated values of 1.6x10^5 RNA structures and the number of times they occur in a genotype space of 10^12 sequences
resources.name: 1.6x10^5 RNA structures and their frequency

resources.description: This MATLAB .mat file contains a cell array with two columns. The first column corresponds to a RNA structure and the second column element consists of a list of inversely folded AU-rich sequences for the RNA structure. The file has 25275 RNA structures.
resources.name: 2.5x10^4 RNA structures and their inversely folded AU-rich sequences

resources.description: This MATLAB .mat file contains a cell array with two columns. The first column corresponds to a RNA structure and the second element consists of a list of inversely folded unbiased sequences for the RNA structure. The file has 25275 RNA structures.
resources.name: 2.5x10^4 RNA structures and their inversely folded sequences

resources.name: Minimum Free Energy of RNA structures with 20% sequence GC content

resources.name: Minimum Free Energy of RNA structures with 40% sequence GC content

resources.description: This MATLAB .mat file contains 1 million RNA sequences of 60% GC content, their corresponding structures and the Minimum Free Energies of the structures.
resources.name: Minimum Free Energy of RNA structures with 60% sequence GC content

resources.description: This MATLAB .mat file contains 1 million RNA sequences of 80% GC content, their corresponding structures and the Minimum Free Energies of the structures.
resources.name: Minimum Free Energy of RNA structures with 80% sequence GC content

resources.description: This MATLAB .mat file contains 1 million normal (unbiased) RNA sequences, their corresponding structures and the Minimum Free Energies of the structures.
resources.name: Minimum Free Energy of RNA structures with unbiased sequence GC content

resources.description: A MATLAB .mat file containing one million AU-rich sequences (AU content greater than or equal to 80%) and their RNA structures
resources.name: 10^6 AU-rich RNA sequences and their structures

resources.description:
This MATLAB .mat file contains the results of simulation of population evolution of AU-rich sequences of an RNA structure at the rate of N*μ = 100. The cell array consists of evolved population (N=100) of 20 AU - rich sequences over 10 generations of evolution.
The genotype space used in the evolution was weighted using kappa = 1
resources.name: AU-rich RNA sequences population evolution at the rate of Nμ = 100

resources.description:
This MATLAB .mat file contains the results of simulation of population evolution of AU-rich sequences of an RNA structure at the rate of N*μ = 1. The cell array consists of evolved population (N=10) of 20 AU - rich sequences over 100 generations of evolution.
The genotype space used in the evolution was weighted using kappa = 1
resources.name: AU-rich RNA sequences population evolution at the rate of Nμ = 1

resources.description:
This MATLAB .mat file contains the results of population evolution of RNA sequences of two RNA structures at the rate of Nμ = 1. Every row in this cell array consists of the evolved population(N=10) of 40 RNA sequences - 20 sequences of an RNA structure of high frequency, and 20 sequences of an RNA structure of low frequency, over 100 generations of evolution.
The two rows in the cell array correspond to the data for two different kappa values (0.5 and 1) used to weight the genotype space.
resources.name: RNA sequences population evolution at the rate of Nμ = 1

resources.description:
This MATLAB .mat file contains the results of population evolution of RNA sequences of two RNA structures at the rate of Nμ = 100. Every row in this cell array consists of the evolved population(N=100) of 40 RNA sequences - 20 sequences of an RNA structure of high frequency, and 20 sequences of an RNA structure of low frequency, over 10 generations of evolution.
The three rows in the cell array correspond to the data for three different kappa values (0.5, 1 and 10) used to weight the genotype space.
resources.name: RNA sequences population evolution at the rate of Nμ = 100

organization.description: The Department of Biotechnology at IIT Madras was founded in 2004 with a vision to be recognised as a Department of International repute with a strong interdisciplinary research and teaching base in biological sciences and engineering and an active collaboration with industries and health-care institutions. The department is housed in the ‘Bhupat & Jyoti Mehta School of BioSciences’. The focus of the department includes basic research in modern biotechnology and molecular basis of life processes; enhancing knowledge base and human resource development; and biotechnology for societal development.
